                <note rend="inline" type="source">890G.00/576: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister Resident in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-22T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 22, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Your 89, April 19, 3 p.m. The Department agrees that a written communication
                    to the Foreign Minister is unnecessary at this time. However, there is no
                    objection to your establishing informal contact without instructions on the
                    question of official recognition.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
